The trial for Russell Henderson, accused in the beating death of Matthew Shepard, has been postponed to April 6 due to a scheduling conflict.
Henderson and Aaron McKinney face murder charges and the death penalty if convicted.
Jury selection starts on March 24.
The case has sparked calls for stronger hate-crime laws.
Henderson's attorney claims he was a witness, not a participant in the beating.
The community of Laramie, where the incident occurred, seeks to show its progressive nature.
The trial has drawn attention from gay rights activists and others advocating for bias crime legislation.
